{
  "texts": [
    "We found that silicon participants shared the same top six domains influencing their behaviour: goals, beliefs about consequences, environmental context and resources, beliefs about capabilities, social influences, and behavioural regulation.",
    "Some beliefs were remarkably similar in their content (social Turing test: content).",
    "Silicon participants focused on the importance of physical activity for avoiding heart attacks and talked about various strategies to stay active, such as making activities fun and setting reminders.",
    "They also understand that some discomfort is normal during exercise and were well-informed about diseases.",
    "On the other hand, human participants discussed the negative symptoms they felt from exercising, which made them less inclined to continue."
  ]
}